# JavaScript Standards

## Plain JavaScript Usage

This project uses plain JavaScript without any frameworks. Follow these guidelines:

### Core Principles
- Use vanilla JavaScript (ES6+) features
- Avoid framework-specific code
- Keep dependencies minimal
- Use native browser APIs when possible

### File Structure
- JavaScript files are stored in `public/js/`
- Main entry points:
  - [simple-store-locator-google.js](mdc:public/js/simple-store-locator-google.js)
  - [simple-landing-page-google.js](mdc:public/js/simple-landing-page-google.js)

### Code Style
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations
- Implement proper error handling with try/catch
- Use const/let instead of var
- Follow IIFE pattern for module encapsulation
- Use template literals for string interpolation

### DOM Manipulation
- Use native DOM APIs
- Cache DOM references when reused
- Use event delegation when appropriate
- Implement proper cleanup in event listeners

### API Integration
- Use fetch API for HTTP requests
- Handle API responses with proper error checking
- Implement retry logic for critical operations
- Cache API responses when appropriate

### Security
- Never expose API keys in client-side code
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Implement proper CORS policies
- Sanitize user input

### Performance
- Minimize DOM operations
- Use debouncing for frequent events
- Implement lazy loading where appropriate
- Cache expensive computations

### Testing
- Write unit tests for critical functions
- Test error handling paths
- Verify browser compatibility
- Test performance with large datasets
